I've paid for this app. Please fix. It crashes whenever I click 'get boon'

It works great, but it's literally only for one player. I love munchkin, so I didn't hesitate to buy this app, but I won't pressure my other friends into buying it as well so I can really utilize it. Pen and paper it is.

Most of the features work well, but the app crashes when you try to create a custom counter.  I saw one review from 2014 where the reviewer emailed them to see when it would be fixed.  The reply was that an update was in the works, but may take a while.  So, it's been 2 years now and still no update.  This is such a simple app that if it takes their developer over 2 years to fix one feature either he is the worst developer on the face of the earth or they are just flat out lying.  I tend to think it's the latter.  Steve Jackson got his money, and he knows that schmucks will keep buying this app because it is the "official" Munchkin app, so why bother spending the pocket change it would cost to fix the app.   This would have been a 4 or 5 star app if they had simply left out the custom counter feature. But when you leave in a broken feature and have no plans to fix it you get 2 stars, and you should consider yourself lucky to get that many.  Where's a curse card when you need one!
Have audio problems after upgrading to marshmallow have tried reinstallation still great to annoy my friends whenever we play and I get an advantage.

This helps me a bunch because numbers get confusing for me. Having a way to count up my combat strength and the monsters really helps keep things straight for me. Love the boons; my favorites are the ones that allow you to make a token into a game piece that adds to your combat strength. I love using a doctor who token as my spirit guide!! :-)
I live this game and the counter really enhances my enjoyment. And getting a boon is awesome!
One player. Expensive. Many better free apps.
Free apps have more to offer not worth the money.
All the boon pictures are pixelated when the rest of the app has good graphics

This app is total bunk. Clearly the creators are just trying to take advantage of their captive audience. Not only would every player have to pay $5 just to keep track of their own level but it doesn't even have all of the specialty packs. Either include a game board level counter in your munchkin games or provide an app the can keep track of all the players levels equally. I just lost a lot of respect for Steve Jackson Games.
Seriously could have put multi player function in.
The ability to claim a boon is worth the price of admission.
The level counter only goes to 2, other than that its a pretty cool addition to the munchkin game

This app is great for tracking your level, but the Kill-o-meter doesn't really do much then store two numbers. The bonuses are very general to apply to any munchkin game, for $5 I expected game specific but bonuses. But works okay as a level tracker, I just expected more
Seems a bit short sighted to not have level counters for at least three Munchkins. Please fix this oversight.

For $5, the app should include ability to track other players levels as well, not just your own. At this rate, I need to shell out an additional $15 for me an my small family to take advantage of this app? No thanks. Other apps That do the same thing are free.
If the level counter also had a bonus counter and an easier to use kill-o-meter that automatically took those 2 stats I would rate it higher.
Friends are jerks and won't let me use the boon. So app it's useless
I love using this when playing Munchkin. However, the app crashes when I try to set up a custom level counter.
This app will continuously ask you if it wants to reset while you are using it. Just use a pen and paper.
Unusable bc the resolution is wrong and everything is to big to use. Wish I could give it 0 stars.

I love munchkin so much so I decided to donate 5 dollars to Steve Jackson's games by buying this. It counts your levels, rolls dice, and gives you boons. It would be nice for level and combat level be on the same page as other level counting apps do this. Also it crashes when I try to make a new counter. Otherwise It works fine but using paper and pennies work just fine.

While I was skeptical on the price, it really is a fun app to have when playing Munchkin with friends.  It covers Epic Munchkin as well as original (20 instead of 10 levels), and some other Steve Jackson games besides.  The little bonuses it gives the player are especially fun -- mostly for the effect they have on your friends when you invoke them!  (Not fair!  lol)
Can help you sneak in a win just when you lost all hope!

A bit overpriced for what it does... I think you should make the dice cheat for you or something, like if you make a weird sequence of taps the dice rolls six... It would be worth the money if you add another boon or something.
My friends and I play this game a lot, and I don't always have something to count my levels with. This app is great! I use it every time I play and the free boon is amazing and extremely helpful.
We have been using this app for ages and you think that they might add cuthulu or some of the the newer sets
Love this app. But i would like to use the custom screen, however it crashes every time... On every device.

This is really really amazingly terrible. Such a disappointment. It looks really outdated. I would've said it looks outdated 3 years ago. It has an easily reproducible crash. It's just bad. I hope you guys update this soon. I love Munchkin and I'm more than happy to give you $5 for a simple app like this, but for that price this should be flawless.
Yes

For $4.99, it REALLY needs to be able to support multiple players. Also, having the ability to set your character's strength by items instead of just a number would be nice.

The idea is that it gives the owner a completely unfair advantage and the abillity to easily track their level and strength. Make sure you know what something is  meant to do BEFORE saying it sucks.

This great little app has a kilometer, a-level counter and a dice roller you can even shake the phone to reset a kilometer or re roll the dice it also has counters for various other Steve Jackson games including epic munchkin and you can customize your own counter. it has a few sound effects and a few animations and it has boons that get more powerful the higher level you are when you claim it.  If you love the game munchkin this is a great little app and its very munchkiny hope you have fun!

App Force Closes when you try to use a Boon.  Mind you i love munchkins and this is truly a sad day. The only reason i bought this app was to support Steve Jackson and the world of Munchkin. The interface is great, its beautifully designed, But it doesn't function the way it is designed to. Truly a sad day. I will keep the App and hope for an update soon, so the app actually works. Sad day...

I would think for a paid app, I would get more functionality.  I tried Munch Level for free.  You can manage multiple players, their levels, item mods etc.  The combat tool will auto-level if you win.  I do like Munchkin itself, thank you Tabletop!  I find the features in SJ's version seems to want to sell more products i.e. the Kill-o-Meter.  Maybe if SJ Games would some of those features, especially for tablet users, then it might be a better app all around!
Worth it just to show your Munchkin Pride.  The in game bonus has helped me win more than once.
